content.text:
Perfect! All three files should now compile. The correct modifier order is:

```swift
}
.safeAreaInset(edge: .bottom) {
    // bottom content
}
.withDesignTheme()
.brandBackground(.auth)
.navigationBarBackButtonHidden(true)
```

The key insight is that `.safeAreaInset()` is a special modifier that takes a closure, so it needs to come first, then after its closing brace `}` we can apply the other modifiers.

## ✅ Final Fix - Correct Modifier Order

All 3 onboarding files now have the correct structure:

```swift
var body: some View {
    VStack {
        // content
    }
    .safeAreaInset(edge: .bottom) {
        // bottom bar content
    }                              // ← closes safeAreaInset
    .withDesignTheme()             // ← applies to whole view
    .brandBackground(.auth)        // ← applies to whole view
    .navigationBarBackButtonHidden(true)
}
```

All compilation errors should now be resolved! 🎉

